King James Version</TITLE><link rel=stylesheet href=style1.css type=text/css>   
</HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James    
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B51C002.htm'>Colossians 2</A></P><CENTER><H2            
ALIGN=CENTER>The Epistle of Paul to the Colossians</H2></CENTER><P><A           
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 3</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>If ye then be risen with MASHIYACH, 
seek those things which are above, where MASHIYACH sitteth on the right hand of 
ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Set   
your affection on things above, not on things on the earth.</P></TD></TR><TR>   
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>For ye are dead, and your life  
is hid with MASHIYACH in ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4>   
<H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>When MASHIYACH, who is our life, shall appear, then shall 
ye also appear with him in glory.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5>   
<H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Mortify therefore your members which are upon the earth;  
fornication, uncleanness, inordinate affection, evil concupiscence, and         
covetousness, which is idolatry:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>
6</H4></TD><TD><P>For which things' sake the wrath of ELOHIYM cometh on the     
children of disobedience:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4> 
</TD><TD><P>In the which ye also walked some time, when ye lived in them.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>But now ye also   
put off all these; anger, wrath, malice, blasphemy, filthy communication out of 
your mouth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>   
Lie not one to another, seeing that ye have put off the old man with his        
deeds;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>And   
have put on the new man, which is renewed in knowledge after the image of him   
that created him:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>Where there is neither Greek nor Jew, circumcision nor uncircumcision,   
Barbarian, Scythian, bond nor free: but MASHIYACH is all, and in all.</P></TD>  
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Put on therefore, as 
the elect of ELOHIYM, holy and beloved, bowels of mercies, kindness, humbleness 
of mind, meekness, longsuffering;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13>  
<H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>Forbearing one another, and forgiving one another, if    
any man have a quarrel against any: even as MASHIYACH forgave you, so also do   
ye.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>And      
above all these things put on charity, which is the bond of perfectness.</P>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>And let the     
peace of ELOHIYM rule in your hearts, to the which also ye are called in one    
body; and be ye thankful.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>      
16</H4></TD><TD><P>Let the word of MASHIYACH dwell in you richly in all wisdom; 
teaching and admonishing one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs,   
singing with grace in your hearts to the ADONAY.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>And whatsoever ye do in word or   
deed, do all in the name of the ADONAY YAHSHUA, giving thanks to ELOHIYM and    
the Father by him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as it is fit in the     
ADONAY.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>     
Husbands, love your wives, and be not bitter against them.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>Children, obey your parents in    
all things: for this is well pleasing unto the ADONAY.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Fathers, provoke not your         
children to anger, lest they be discouraged.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>Servants, obey in all things your masters       
according to the flesh; not with eyeservice, as menpleasers; but in singleness  
of heart, fearing ELOHIYM;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>     
23</H4></TD><TD><P>And whatsoever ye do, do it heartily, as to the ADONAY, and  
not unto men;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>Knowing that of the ADONAY ye shall receive the reward of the inheritance:   
for ye serve the ADONAY MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25> 
<H4>25</H4></TD><TD><P>But he that doeth wrong shall receive for the wrong      
which he hath done: and there is no respect of persons.</P></TD></TR></TABLE>   
